---
import ArchiveEntry from "#components/ArchiveEntry.astro";
import PageHeading from "#components/PageHeading.astro";
import GlobalLayout from "#layouts/GlobalLayout.astro";
---

<GlobalLayout title="Archive">
	<PageHeading
		eyebrowText="Older versions of the exact website you're on right now"
		>Visions of websites past</PageHeading
	>

	<div class="sites">
		<ArchiveEntry year="2014–2015">
			<p class="title">Version 0</p>

			<p>
				The code for this version is (perhaps fortunately) lost to time. The
				only thing I remember about it is that it had similar navigation to v1.
				And that it was built as a student project using student design work.
				That&apos;s called efficiency.
			</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://jquery.com/">jQuery</a>, I assume.
			</p>
		</ArchiveEntry>

		<ArchiveEntry year="2015–2017"
			><p class="title"><a href="https://v1.lowmess.com/">Version 1</a></p>

			<p>
				Mostly this was a showcase for the design work I did as a student, but
				if you look closely you can find some client work. The copy (and color
				contrast) on this site is really bad, and I find it&apos;s best to not
				think about the quality of the code.
			</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://prepros.io/">Prepros</a>, <a
					href="https://pugjs.org/">Pug (née Jade)</a
				>,
				<a href="https://sass-lang.com">Sass</a>, and <a
					href="https://jquery.com/">jQuery</a
				>.
			</p></ArchiveEntry
		>

		<ArchiveEntry year="2017"
			><p class="title"><a href="https://v2.lowmess.com/">Version 2</a></p>

			<p>
				The first portfolio I made as a developer. I hated the design on this
				one basically as soon as I launched it, and it lasted fewer than 6
				months before I scrapped it for v3.
			</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://rollupjs.org">Rollup</a>, <a
					href="https://metalsmith.io">Metalsmith</a
				>, <a href="https://pugjs.org">Pug</a>, <a href="https://postcss.org"
					>PostCSS</a
				>, and <a href="http://tachyons.io">Tachyons</a>.
			</p></ArchiveEntry
		>

		<ArchiveEntry year="2017–2020">
			<p class="title"><a href="https://v3.lowmess.com/">Version 3</a></p>

			<p>
				This design proved popular, and several developers forked the repo and
				used it as a basis for their own sites. However it proved limiting when
				I wanted to implement dark mode. Also I got bored of it (the
				Designer&apos;s Curse&trade;).
			</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://gatsbyjs.com">Gatsby</a>, <a
					href="https://preactjs.com">Preact</a
				>, <a href="https://mdxjs.com">MDX</a>, and <a
					href="https://rebassjs.org">Rebass</a
				>.
			</p>
		</ArchiveEntry>

		<ArchiveEntry year="2020–2024">
			<p class="title">
				<a href="https://v4.lowmess.com/">Version 4</a> &amp; <a
					href="https://v4-1.lowmess.com/">Version 4.1</a
				>
			</p>

			<p>
				This design survived a change of framework (<a
					href="/blog/migrate-gatsby-next">Gatsby to Next.js</a
				>). The star of the show was something relegated to the about page in
				v3: a rolling 30-day stat aggregation. Unfortunately, several sites
				restricting API access crippled the homepage.
			</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://gatsbyjs.com">Gatsby</a>/<a
					href="https://nextjs.org">Next.js</a
				>, <a href="https://preactjs.com">Preact</a>, <a
					href="https://mdxjs.com">MDX</a
				>, and <a href="https://theme-ui.com">Theme UI</a>.
			</p>
		</ArchiveEntry>

		<ArchiveEntry year="2025–">
			<p class="title"><a href="/">Version 5</a></p>

			<p>It&apos;s the site you are currently looking at.</p>

			<p class="tooling">
				Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and <a
					href="https://mdxjs.com">MDX</a
				>.
			</p>
		</ArchiveEntry>
	</div>
</GlobalLayout>

<style>
	.sites {
		display: grid;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: var(--rhythm-md);

		@media (min-width: 32em) {
			grid-template-columns: max-content calc(var(--outline-width) * 3) 1fr;
			column-gap: var(--content-padding);
			row-gap: var(--rhythm-lg);
		}
	}

	.title {
		font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
		line-height: var(--line-height-heading);
		font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.tooling {
		font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
	}

	p {
		margin: 0;
		max-width: 50ch;
		text-wrap: pretty;
	}

	p + p {
		margin-block-start: var(--rhythm-md);
	}

	a {
		color: var(--color-text);
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-primary);

		&:hover {
			color: var(--color-primary);
		}
	}
</style>
